obo:ECO_0000279  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_3670  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Analyzing parallel fiber inputs to Purkinje cells, Fig.3A shows that most vGLUT1 puncta overlapped with the punctate contactin-6 staining. Dense contactin-6 puncta were apposed to dendritic mGluR1a of Purkinje cells. These data support a presynaptic localization of contactin-6.\n\n21/6/2017 Pim\n- The rationale is:\n(1) protein expressed in axons (parallel fibers).\n(2) colocalization with pre- and postsynaptic marker proteins.\n(3) localization in synaptosomal preparations.\n- Although superresolution data is not presented, based on cell type expression and colocalization data the authors conclude: \"Col-lectively, these results indicate that NB-3 is localized presynaptically at glutamatergic synapses.\". Experimental description: \"Mice were anesthetized with pentobarbital and transcardially\nperfused\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3670" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

